  "prompt": "What is the difference between Brabus versus AMG in Mercedes Benz?",
  "response": "Brabus and AMG are both high-performance tuning companies, but they have some key differences:\n\nAMG:\n- Official in-house performance division of Mercedes-Benz\n- Fully integrated with Mercedes-Benz\n- Offers factory-authorized performance modifications\n- Vehicles are designed and engineered directly by Mercedes\n- Maintains factory warranty\n- More widely available globally\n- Focuses on performance and sporty driving dynamics\n- Typically more conservative in modifications\n\nBrabus:\n- Independent aftermarket tuning company\n- Not directly owned by Mercedes-Benz\n- Specializes in extreme performance modifications\n- Often more radical and aggressive tuning\n- Can void factory warranty\n- Less widely available\n- Known for creating ultra-high-performance and luxury versions of Mercedes vehicles\n- Tends to offer more extensive modifications, including body kits, interior upgrades, and significant engine enhancements\n- Often produces more powerful and more expensive versions of standard Mercedes models\n\nIn essence, AMG is an official Mercedes performance brand, while Brabus is an independent tuning company that specializes in modifying Mercedes vehicles to higher performance and luxury standards.",
